result.execSummary:
The defendant Gail S Onasch was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Gail S Onasch is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Gail S Onasch was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

AS TO COUNT 2 AS AMENDED:   Court finds this is not a domestic abuse incident and struck the Domestic Abuse enhancer.   Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he/she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  
*
Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 3 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence with credit for 3 days time served.  THIS IS A TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.  Court ordered costs set at a amount not to exceed $500.00 inclusive.  Court found the Domestic Abuse surcharge is NOT applicable. Court waived the DNA surcharge as a sample was not taken.  Cash bail on deposit to apply.
